Failing test: "should bring a dead cell to life that has exactly 3 live neighbors (reproduction)"
Expected behavior: Given [[0,0], [1,0], [0,1]], dead cell [1,1] has 3 live neighbors and should become alive. The test asserts result contains [1, 1].
Current error: expected [[0,0],[1,0],[0,1]] to deep equally contain [1, 1]
Implementation file: src/game-of-life.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
const isNeighbor = (cell: number[], other: number[]): boolean =>
  !(other[0] === cell[0] && other[1] === cell[1]) &&
  Math.abs(other[0] - cell[0]) <= 1 &&
  Math.abs(other[1] - cell[1]) <= 1;

const countNeighbors = (cell: number[], liveCells: number[][]): number =>
  liveCells.filter((other) => isNeighbor(cell, other)).length;

export function nextGeneration(liveCells: number[][]): number[][] {
  return liveCells.filter((cell) => {
    const neighborCount = countNeighbors(cell, liveCells);
    return neighborCount === 2 || neighborCount === 3;
  });
}
```

The implementation needs to add reproduction logic: find all dead cells adjacent to any live cell, check if they have exactly 3 live neighbors, and include them in the result. This requires:
1. Collect all candidate dead cells (neighbors of live cells that aren't themselves live)
2. For each candidate, count its live neighbors
3. If count is exactly 3, include it in the result

